    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Mideast Peace, Derailed Again</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Amir H Wolfe letter asks why world accepts that Jew living in Hebron or visiting Temple Mount are 'provocation'; say too many facts on the ground point to sad conclusion that peace is not true goal of Palestinians</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Unapologetic, Sharon Rejects Blame for Igniting Violence'' (news article, Oct. 5):</p>
        <p>First, the world accepted as fact that Jews living in Hebron were a provocation. Today, Jews visiting the Temple Mount are a provocation.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Unapologetic, Sharon Rejects Blame for Igniting Violence'' (news article, Oct. 5):</p>
        <p>First, the world accepted as fact that Jews living in Hebron were a provocation. Today, Jews visiting the Temple Mount are a provocation.</p>
        <p>Tomorrow, will the presence of Jews in the Galilee be viewed as a provocation?</p>
        <p>Thus, the whole fallacy of a peace process unfolds. It is time that someone said, ''The king has no clothes.''  It is time to reassess what the true motives and goals of Palestinians are. Too many facts on the ground point to the sad conclusion that it is not peace.</p>
        <p>AMIR H. WOLFE  Silver Spring, Md., Oct. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
